<section xml:id="section-projection-terminology">

<title>Terminology and notation</title>

<p><dl width="narrow">

	<li>
	<title>orthogonal projection (of a vector <m>\uvec{v}</m> onto a subspace <m>U</m>)</title>
	<idx><h>orthogonal</h><h>projection (onto a subspace in an inner product space)</h></idx>
	<idx><h>projection</h><h>onto a subspace in an inner product space</h></idx>
	<p>
	the vector <m>\uvec{u}</m> in <m>U</m> in the unique decomposition
	<me> \uvec{v} = \uvec{u} + \uvec{u}' </me>
	of <m>\uvec{v}</m> into the sum of a vector in <m>U</m> and a vector in <m>\orthogcmp{U}</m>;
	sometimes called the
	<term>vector component of <m>\uvec{v}</m> parallel to <m>U</m></term>
	<idx><h>component</h><h>parallel (to a subspace of an inner product space)</h></idx>
	<idx><h>parallel</h><h>component (to a subspace of an inner product space)</h></idx>
	</p>
	</li>

	<li>
	<title>vector component of a vector <m>\uvec{v}</m> orthogonal to a subspace <m>U</m></title>
	<idx><h>orthogonal</h><h>component (to a subspace of an inner product space)</h></idx>
	<idx><h>component</h><h>orthogonal (to a subspace of an inner product space)</h></idx>
	<p> the vector <m>\proj_{\orthogcmp{U}} \uvec{v} = \uvec{v} - \proj_U \uvec{v}</m> </p>
	</li>

	<li>
	<title>best approximation (to a vector <m>\uvec{v}</m> from within a subspace <m>U</m>)</title>
	<idx>best approximation</idx>
	<p> the orthogonal projection <m>\proj_U \uvec{v}</m> </p>
	</li>

	<li xml:id="definition-projection-distance-vec-subsp">
	<title>distance between a vector <m>\uvec{v}</m> and a subspace <m>U</m></title>
	<idx><h>distance</h><h>between a vector and a subspace</h></idx>
	<p>
	the smallest possible value of <m>\dist (\uvec{v}, \uvec{u})</m>
	amongst all vectors <m>\uvec{u}</m> in <m>U</m>,
	denoted <m>\dist (\uvec{v}, U)</m>
	</p>
	</li>

	<li>
	<title>normal system (associated to an inconsistent system <m>A \uvec{x} = \uvec{b}</m>)</title>
	<idx><h>normal</h><h>system</h></idx>
	<idx><h>system</h><h>normal</h></idx>
	<p> the transformed system <m>\utrans{A} A \uvec{x} = \utrans{A} \uvec{b}</m> </p>
	</li>

	<li>
	<title>least-squares solution (for an inconsistent system)</title>
	<idx>least-squares solution</idx>
	<idx><h>solution</h><h>least-squares</h></idx>
	<p> a solution to the normal system associated to the inconsistent system </p>
	</li>

	<li>
	<title>pseudo-inverse matrix (of a possibly non-square matrix <m>A</m>)</title>
	<idx>pseudo-inverse matrix</idx>
	<idx><h>inverse</h><h>pseudo-</h></idx>
	<p> the matrix <m>\inv{(\utrans{A} A)} \utrans{A}</m>, in the case that <m>\utrans{A} A</m> is invertible </p>
	</li>

</dl></p>

</section>
